Let $x,$ $y,$ and $z$ denote $\tfrac{a}{b},$ $\tfrac{a}{c},$ and $\tfrac{b}{c},$ respectively. Since $a,$ $b,$ and $c$ are positive, we can express them as multiples of another variable, say, $k$. Hence,
  \begin{align*}
  a &= xk \\
  b &= yk \\
  c &= zk
\end{align*}
Clearly, if any of $x,$ $y,$ and $z$ equal $0,$ the fraction reduces to $0.$ For example,
  \begin{align*}
  \frac{(a + b)(a + c)(b + c)}{abc} &= \frac{(xk + yk)(xk + zk)(yk + zk)}{(xk)(yk)(zk)} \\
  &= \frac{k^3(x + y)k^2(x + z)k^2(y + z)}{(x)(y)(z)k^3} \\
  &= k^2\frac{(x + y)(x + z)(y + z)}{(x)(y)(z)}
\end{align*}
But if any of the numbers in question are equal to $0,$ the fraction does equal $0.$ Thus, the minimum value will not be negative. Since every number in question is positive is 
    \[\frac{(x + y)(x + z)(y + z)}{(x)(y)(z)}\]
We first manipulate this equation:
  \begin{align*}
    \frac{(x + y)(x + z)(y + z)}{(x)(y)(z)}
    &= \frac{x^2y + x^2z + xy^2 + y^2z + yz^2 + zx^2 + 2xyz}{xyz} \\
    &= \frac{x^2y}{xyz} + \frac{x^2z}{xyz} + \frac{xy^2}{xyz} + \frac{y^2z}{xyz} + \frac{yz^2}{xyz} + \frac{zx^2}{xyz} + \frac{2xyz}{xyz} \\
    &= \frac{x}{z} + \frac{x}{y} + \frac{y}{z} + \frac{y}{x} + \frac{z}{x} + \frac{z}{y} + 2 \\
    &= z^{-1}x + x^{-1}z + z^{-1}y + y^{-1}z + y^{-1}x + x^{-1}y + 2 \\
    &= z^{-1}(x + y + xz + yz) + x^{-1}(y + z + xy + yz) + y^{-1}(z + x + zy + xz) + 2 \\
    &= z^{-1}\{x(1 + z) + y(1 + z)\} + x^{-1}\{y(1 + x) + z(1 + x)\} + y^{-1}\{z(1 + y) + x(1 + y)\} + 2 \\
    &= z^{-1}\{x(1 + z)\}(1 + y^{-1}) + x^{-1}\{y(1 + x)\}(1 + z^{-1}) + y^{-1}\{z(1 + y)\}(1 + x^{-1}) + 2
        \end{align*}
So
  \begin{align*}
    \frac{(x + y)(x + z)(y + z)}{(x)(y)(z)}
    &= z^{-1}\{x(1 + z)\}(1 + y^{-1}) + x^{-1}\{y(1 + x)\}(1 + z^{-1}) + y^{-1}\{z(1 +
      y)\}(1 + x^{-1}) + z^{-1} + x^{-1} + y^{-1} + 1 \\
    &\ge 3\sqrt[3]{z^{-1}x(1 + z)x^{-1}y(1 + x)y^{-1}z(1 + y)} + 3 \cdot (z^{-1}x(1 + z)^{-1})^{1/3} \\
    &\ge 3
  \end{align*}
